headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 37 points and 13 rebounds to the tune of “MVP! MVP!” chants and the Philadelphia 76ers inched closer toward securing the top spot in the East with a 109-107 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid strengthens MVP bid, 76ers hold off Pelicans 109-107

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine and Coby White each scored 25 points and the Chicago Bulls overcame a big effort by Kemba Walker to beat the Boston Celtics 121-99 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, White score 25 as Bulls beat Celtics 121-99

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 28 points, LaMelo Ball added 27 points and the Charlotte Hornets inched closer to securing a spot in the play-in tournament with a 122-112 win over the Orlando Magic on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets top Magic 122-112, inch closer to play-in tournament

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro returned after a six-game absence and scored 27 points, Jimmy Butler had 25 and the Miami Heat moved back into the No. 6 spot in the Eastern Conference, beating the Minnesota Timberwolves 121-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat move back into 6th in East, top Timberwolves 121-112

headlines.description: — Brook Lopez had 24 points and Khris Middleton scored 21 of his 23 in the second half to help the Milwaukee Bucks beat the short-handed Houston Rockets 141-133 on Friday night for their fifth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Rockets 141-133, tie Nets for 2nd place in East

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 24 points in 23 minutes and the Dallas Mavericks kept the prime spot in a tight race to avoid the Western Conference play-in tournament with a breezy 110-90 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs cruise past Cavs 110-90 to stay in 5th in West

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored a career-high 48 points to rally the Utah Jazz past the Denver Nuggets 127-120 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogdanovic scores career-high 48 points, Jazz beat Nuggets

events.name: New York Knicks at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton scored 26 points, a feisty Chris Paul added 17 points and 11 assists and the Phoenix Suns stayed in the hunt for the top record in the NBA by beating the New York Knicks 128-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns stay in hunt for NBA's top record, beat Knicks 128-105

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 38 points to lead Portland to a 106-101 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Friday night that gave the Trail Blazers the tiebreaker over their Western Conference foe as the season winds to a close.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blazers get key tiebreaker with 106-101 win over Lakers

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray scored 10 of his 22 points in the fourth quarter and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Sacramento Kings 113-104 on Friday night to end a five-game losing streak and strengthen their hold on the final playoff spot in the West.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs hold off Kings 113-104 to end five-game slide
